OL,3,CExtra #505 million for Wales in
OL,4,CChancellor's Autumn Budget
OL,6,FIn Wales, this is estimated to affect
OL,7,Fmore than 65,000 children in Wales,
OL,8,F11% of all children.
OL,10,FThe removal of the two child limit
OL,11,Fmeans households could receive around
OL,12,F#3,500 per year for each additional
OL,13,Fchild in benefits.
OL,15,FFirst Minister Eluned Morgan has
OL,16,Fpraised the Chancellor's "bold action
OL,17,Fto scrap the two-child limit.
