OL,3,CExtra #505 million for Wales in
OL,4,CChancellor's Autumn Budget
OL,6,F"I'm pleased the Chancellor is taking
OL,7,Fbold action to scrap the two-child
OL,8,Flimit, which will help to tackle the
OL,9,Fscourge of child poverty. This is
OL,10,Fsomething we have called for since it
OL,11,Fwas introduced under the previous UK
OL,12,FGovernment. It will make a real
OL,13,Fdifference to so many families and the
OL,14,Flives of children all over Wales.
OL,16,F"I welcome the additional support with
OL,17,Fenergy bills. We have also called on
OL,18,Fthe UK Government to continue to
OL,19,Fsupport Wales with extra money for
OL,20,Fpublic services.
